WEBVTT

00:00:03.970 --> 00:00:05.040
If we undo that first D-mail...

00:00:05.040 --> 00:00:06.070
Being Meltdown
If we undo that first D-mail...

00:00:06.070 --> 00:00:06.920
Being Meltdown

00:00:06.920 --> 00:00:09.020
You will die.
Being Meltdown

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:48.090
So, there you are.

00:01:49.060 --> 00:01:52.240
If you keep lying there, you'll get heatstroke.

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:55.520
You sleep on the roof of the lab 
all the time, don't you?

00:01:56.420 --> 00:01:57.720
Besides, it's cloudy now.

00:01:58.230 --> 00:02:00.120
Did you see Mayuri?

00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:02.430
Hashida said he couldn't find her at Comima...

00:02:02.970 --> 00:02:04.130
Yeah.

00:02:04.130 --> 00:02:06.020
I met up with her after that.

00:02:07.170 --> 00:02:08.140
I see.

00:02:12.490 --> 00:02:14.600
Hey, Okabe...

00:02:14.600 --> 00:02:15.550
What?

00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:23.970
All right.

00:02:28.350 --> 00:02:29.280
Hey.

00:02:31.310 --> 00:02:32.520
It's raining.

00:02:38.010 --> 00:02:39.850
WTF?!

00:02:46.340 --> 00:02:48.390
Why didn't you warn me earlier?

00:02:48.390 --> 00:02:51.160
I'm soaked, down to my underwear...

00:02:51.160 --> 00:02:52.430
I did tell you.

00:02:52.980 --> 00:02:54.640
It's your fault, Christina, for not listen—

00:03:00.760 --> 00:03:02.380
Y-You pervert!

00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:05.260
I wasn't trying to look...

00:03:05.600 --> 00:03:08.020
And it's your fault for wearing such thin clothes.

00:03:08.020 --> 00:03:10.490
I'd forgotten you were such a pervert.

00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:13.720
Who'd want to see your stick figure in the nude...

00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:17.510
One more word, and I turn 
your neocortex into a flower pot!

00:03:17.510 --> 00:03:18.640
What kind of threat is that?

00:03:18.640 --> 00:03:19.770
Stay away from me!

00:03:21.660 --> 00:03:23.010
What's that?

00:03:24.410 --> 00:03:26.890
I got scratched somewhere, 
when I was looking for you...

00:03:27.570 --> 00:03:28.560
Klutz!

00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:31.320
I'm classified as a "mad scientist"...

00:03:31.320 --> 00:03:32.390
Right, right!

00:03:32.390 --> 00:03:34.630
You're so much trouble...

00:03:34.630 --> 00:03:35.720
Hand that over.

00:03:35.720 --> 00:03:37.590
I have a sewing kit on me.

00:03:37.590 --> 00:03:38.640
I'll fix it up.

00:03:39.030 --> 00:03:40.830
A sewing kit?

00:03:40.830 --> 00:03:42.910
I consider myself more family-oriented

00:03:42.910 --> 00:03:44.610
than most people.

00:03:44.610 --> 00:03:45.930
Take it off.

00:03:47.850 --> 00:03:49.520
Just to be clear,

00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:52.610
it's dark, so don't expect too much.

00:03:52.610 --> 00:03:56.410
And you can look forward to finding out, 
after we leave, what color thread I used.

00:03:56.850 --> 00:03:58.890
Black, red, pink...

00:03:58.890 --> 00:04:00.560
You have a 33% chance of each one.

00:04:01.030 --> 00:04:03.180
I'll just pray it isn't pink.

00:04:03.780 --> 00:04:05.420
Stay back.

00:04:05.420 --> 00:04:06.330
Don't worry.

00:04:06.330 --> 00:04:07.920
I'm not interested in that stick figure of yours...

00:04:07.920 --> 00:04:09.640
I told you... A flower pot!

00:04:12.830 --> 00:04:13.770
Jeez...

00:04:14.330 --> 00:04:17.310
Where did you have to go, 
to rip your clothes like this?

00:04:18.460 --> 00:04:21.220
Today, I went to the lab,

00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:22.440
the laundry,

00:04:22.440 --> 00:04:23.470
a walk.

00:04:24.070 --> 00:04:27.730
And then to your hotel.

00:04:27.730 --> 00:04:29.980
The hotel? You stopped by?

00:04:30.350 --> 00:04:31.760
It's your fault.

00:04:32.410 --> 00:04:34.460
You wouldn't answer my messages.

00:04:34.460 --> 00:04:36.060
You weren't picking up your phone.

00:04:36.060 --> 00:04:38.210
Were you worried about me...

00:04:38.210 --> 00:04:42.460
As head of the lab, 
it's my job to keep track of my assistant.

00:04:47.150 --> 00:04:48.460
It isn't done yet?

00:04:48.460 --> 00:04:49.600
Almost...

00:04:50.120 --> 00:04:50.620
Here!

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:52.810
That's cold. Hey!

00:04:52.810 --> 00:04:53.640
Just put it on.

00:04:53.830 --> 00:04:57.920
I'm not interested in the stick figure 
of a nude mad scientist.

00:05:07.350 --> 00:05:09.770
It was probably around here, right?

00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:17.100
The place I was stabbed...

00:05:20.250 --> 00:05:21.920
How did you know?

00:05:22.570 --> 00:05:29.400
The pain and despair were too real for a dream.

00:05:30.060 --> 00:05:32.810
Kurisu. You can't mean...

00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:38.790
I have hazy memories inside.

00:05:39.450 --> 00:05:43.430
Weak, almost nonexistent memories...

00:05:44.950 --> 00:05:47.250
Not just of being stabbed.

00:05:47.840 --> 00:05:51.350
I remember you, too... hazily...

00:05:52.020 --> 00:05:54.560
How desperate you were to save Mayuri.

00:05:55.400 --> 00:05:57.670
How you kept pressing forward,

00:05:57.670 --> 00:06:00.310
even hurt and all alone.

00:06:00.710 --> 00:06:03.300
You haven't made it back to your original world,

00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:05.690
but you've kept going,

00:06:05.690 --> 00:06:08.560
kept calling her name,

00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:10.310
kept crying...

00:06:11.060 --> 00:06:13.930
Kept trying to save her.

00:06:14.670 --> 00:06:16.680
Every time I see that face,

00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:20.970
I think about how important she is to you...

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:23.980
And about whether it's possible for someone

00:06:25.040 --> 00:06:29.680
to truly care for another person that much...

00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:36.900
That's why I wanted to work with you.

00:06:36.900 --> 00:06:39.470
That's why I wanted to help you.

00:06:44.630 --> 00:06:48.310
Okabe, save Mayuri.

00:06:50.270 --> 00:06:53.720
You must save her.

00:06:55.980 --> 00:07:01.250
If we go to the beta world line, you'll die!

00:07:04.380 --> 00:07:07.600
But it's the only way...

00:07:08.770 --> 00:07:11.100
You know that better than anyone, right?

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:13.030
There's only one option.

00:07:13.030 --> 00:07:14.110
You!

00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:16.800
You're telling me to abandon you?

00:07:16.800 --> 00:07:18.710
Is there another way?

00:07:21.900 --> 00:07:24.060
I've been thinking about the following since yesterday...

00:07:24.620 --> 00:07:27.600
"Isn't there some other way?"

00:07:27.980 --> 00:07:30.740
"Isn't there something else we can do?"

00:07:30.740 --> 00:07:35.070
But this time, I can't come up with anything...

00:07:35.070 --> 00:07:38.760
Except going to the beta world line.

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:47.360
Okabe!

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:51.960
I refuse to accept this...

00:07:51.960 --> 00:07:53.140
I won't give up!

00:07:54.520 --> 00:07:56.210
<i>I can't...</i>

00:07:56.210 --> 00:07:58.280
<i>I can't abandon Kurisu.</i>

00:07:58.820 --> 00:08:01.520
<i>I can't let her die and then keep living.</i>

00:08:01.520 --> 00:08:03.720
<i>What would the point of that be?</i>

00:08:04.350 --> 00:08:05.420
<i>I...</i>

00:08:06.430 --> 00:08:07.500
<i>I...</i>

00:08:23.220 --> 00:08:25.100
You can run away...

00:08:25.100 --> 00:08:28.220
You can run away, but that'll just make it worse!

00:08:30.140 --> 00:08:31.230
Shut up!

00:08:33.260 --> 00:08:35.350
No matter how many times you time leap,

00:08:35.350 --> 00:08:37.230
you can't get past the 1% barrier!

00:08:37.230 --> 00:08:39.690
We don't know until we try!

00:08:39.690 --> 00:08:42.820
You'll just see Mayuri die!

00:08:42.820 --> 00:08:44.220
Again...

00:08:45.020 --> 00:08:46.890
It'll destroy you.

00:08:46.890 --> 00:08:49.740
It won't...

00:08:50.480 --> 00:08:53.850
How many times do you think I've watched her die?

00:08:54.980 --> 00:08:56.560
I've seen it again...

00:08:57.220 --> 00:09:00.020
And again and again and again

00:09:00.020 --> 00:09:01.430
and again and again...

00:09:03.450 --> 00:09:07.430
It won't destroy me... 
The number of times I see it doesn't matter!

00:09:12.210 --> 00:09:14.560
Do you hear what you're saying?

00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:18.260
Mayuri's going to suffer and die...

00:09:18.260 --> 00:09:20.430
How can you say it doesn't matter?

00:09:21.640 --> 00:09:24.980
If that doesn't affect you,

00:09:24.980 --> 00:09:29.060
then your heart's already broken...

00:09:29.870 --> 00:09:31.430
Just stop...

00:09:31.430 --> 00:09:32.890
Or it really will break you.

00:09:35.010 --> 00:09:36.020
I know.

00:09:37.170 --> 00:09:38.970
I noticed it long ago.

00:09:40.110 --> 00:09:43.610
No matter how many times Mayuri died, 
I stopped being surprised.

00:09:44.470 --> 00:09:47.720
I'd gone numb without even knowing it.

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:53.680
Sometimes, I even waited before time leaping, 
just to see when she'd die.

00:09:54.520 --> 00:09:55.890
At some point,

00:09:55.890 --> 00:09:58.780
it just stopped affecting me.

00:10:00.660 --> 00:10:06.470
Somewhere inside, I was calmly telling myself 
that I could do it over...

00:10:14.610 --> 00:10:16.910
Save her...

00:10:16.910 --> 00:10:20.960
If you don't, it will destroy you.

00:10:20.960 --> 00:10:24.640
If you let her die, you'll regret it... I'm certain!

00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:29.140
You and I have come this far, 
from the single wish to save her!

00:10:29.970 --> 00:10:33.040
If we stop, we'll always regret it.

00:10:33.040 --> 00:10:35.410
But if we save her...

00:10:35.410 --> 00:10:36.220
You'll...

00:10:36.220 --> 00:10:37.660
I'll just go back!

00:10:37.660 --> 00:10:39.890
To the first world line, before the D-mail was sent!

00:10:40.210 --> 00:10:42.020
That's what's best for me...

00:10:42.020 --> 00:10:43.780
And it's what's best for you!

00:10:51.390 --> 00:10:55.120
<i>How many times have we fought, 
over these past twenty days?</i>

00:10:56.380 --> 00:10:58.810
<i>We've made fun of each other.</i>

00:10:59.470 --> 00:11:00.970
<i>We've talked about our problems.</i>

00:11:02.060 --> 00:11:05.220
<i>When my back was against the wall, 
I turned to Kurisu.</i>

00:11:05.990 --> 00:11:08.270
<i>Kurisu was the one who listened to me,</i>

00:11:08.270 --> 00:11:10.770
<i>who believed me...</i>

00:11:11.760 --> 00:11:15.150
<i>At eighteen, a genius with a 
published academic paper.</i>

00:11:15.760 --> 00:11:18.240
<i>Always calm, always strong-willed.</i>

00:11:18.240 --> 00:11:20.530
<i>Always so proud and nosy.</i>

00:11:21.070 --> 00:11:23.600
<i>But always so kind and honest.</i>

00:11:23.600 --> 00:11:27.850
<i>Her theories continually amazed me.</i>

00:11:28.450 --> 00:11:30.640
<i>And I remembered everything she said.</i>

00:11:31.180 --> 00:11:34.560
<i>Watched everything she did...</i>

00:11:36.300 --> 00:11:38.680
<i>She wasn't just another lab member.</i>

00:11:38.680 --> 00:11:40.980
<i>To me, Makise Kurisu was...</i>

00:11:49.650 --> 00:11:54.430
I can't save you...

00:11:55.060 --> 00:11:56.560
I'm sorry.

00:12:01.260 --> 00:12:02.390
Thank you.

00:12:03.220 --> 00:12:07.230
For suffering so much for me...

00:12:09.170 --> 00:12:11.440
Why was it you?

00:12:12.110 --> 00:12:14.270
Why you?!

00:12:15.870 --> 00:12:20.430
Hey, what does it mean to change world lines?

00:12:21.180 --> 00:12:25.140
Maybe the second you go to the beta world line,

00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:29.050
you'll just disappear from this world.

00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:32.800
Or maybe you trade places with another Okabe.

00:12:33.460 --> 00:12:36.850
That doesn't matter...

00:12:37.390 --> 00:12:39.060
That's not true.

00:12:39.060 --> 00:12:40.940
I'm not dead.

00:12:40.940 --> 00:12:44.100
Even if I'm dead in the beta world line,

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:47.340
there's no guarantee that I'm going to die here!

00:12:47.340 --> 00:12:49.000
There could be another me,

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:51.210
amidst all the other, infinite world lines.

00:12:51.210 --> 00:12:55.270
And our minds are connected and comprise "me."

00:12:56.860 --> 00:13:00.270
Don't you think that'd be wonderful?

00:13:01.970 --> 00:13:05.280
You'd be everywhere, in every time, at once.

00:13:05.890 --> 00:13:08.430
A great love for someone,

00:13:08.430 --> 00:13:10.860
a great belief in something,

00:13:10.860 --> 00:13:13.360
a great desire to pass on something...

00:13:13.360 --> 00:13:17.270
If all those things surpass time itself and create "you,"

00:13:18.220 --> 00:13:20.560
wouldn't that be wonderful?

00:13:21.770 --> 00:13:25.140
So don't think of it as abandoning me.

00:13:26.550 --> 00:13:29.540
Even if the world line changes,

00:13:29.540 --> 00:13:32.810
as long as you don't forget me, I'm there.

00:13:33.360 --> 00:13:34.560
So...

00:13:35.410 --> 00:13:38.180
I will never forget you.

00:13:43.000 --> 00:13:47.510
I won't forget the person I care for most.

00:13:47.510 --> 00:13:49.080
Does that mean...

00:13:49.080 --> 00:13:50.050
It's the truth.

00:13:50.050 --> 00:13:53.420
H-How... It's so sudden...

00:13:53.420 --> 00:13:55.960
I'm in love with you.

00:13:57.490 --> 00:13:58.780
What about you?

00:13:58.780 --> 00:14:00.770
What do you mean?

00:14:00.770 --> 00:14:02.180
I want to hear your response.

00:14:02.180 --> 00:14:05.180
How do you feel about me?

00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:10.460
You want to know?

00:14:10.460 --> 00:14:11.640
Yeah.

00:14:11.640 --> 00:14:15.010
Your face... Close your eyes.

00:14:15.010 --> 00:14:15.820
Why?

00:14:15.820 --> 00:14:18.310
Just do it!

00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:51.020
I-I didn't want to do that, okay?

00:14:51.670 --> 00:14:55.280
But experiences, such as your first kiss,

00:14:55.280 --> 00:14:59.820
that are stored in the hippocampus with your 
strong memories are harder to forget.

00:14:59.820 --> 00:15:00.520
So...

00:15:00.520 --> 00:15:01.910
Too bad.

00:15:02.500 --> 00:15:04.680
That wasn't my first kiss.

00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:07.510
You bratty virgin!

00:15:07.510 --> 00:15:09.160
Shut up, virgin.

00:15:09.160 --> 00:15:13.540
My first kiss wasn't at all romantic.

00:15:14.480 --> 00:15:16.050
Anyway...

00:15:16.050 --> 00:15:18.290
That last one only left a weak impression.

00:15:18.290 --> 00:15:19.140
Once more.

00:15:20.100 --> 00:15:22.200
I don't want to forget, not ever.

00:15:22.200 --> 00:15:24.600
So I'll take extra care.

00:15:25.380 --> 00:15:27.760
Well, I guess that's okay.

00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.970
Just a kiss, right?

00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:37.810
<i>Time is passing so quickly...</i>

00:15:39.430 --> 00:15:43.590
<i>Right now, I feel like complaining to Einstein.</i>

00:15:44.440 --> 00:15:45.930
<i>You know, Okabe...</i>

00:15:45.930 --> 00:15:48.530
<i>Whether time is slow or fast</i>

00:15:48.530 --> 00:15:51.720
<i>depends on perception.</i>

00:15:52.930 --> 00:15:57.430
<i>Relativity theory is so romantic.</i>

00:15:57.890 --> 00:16:00.740
<i>And so sad.</i>

00:16:08.200 --> 00:16:09.510
Goodbye, then.

00:16:09.510 --> 00:16:11.270
Sure about not saying it to Mayuri and Daru?

00:16:11.270 --> 00:16:14.520
Everyone seeing me off would just make it worse.

00:16:14.520 --> 00:16:16.320
If it's only you,

00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:19.030
I can leave Japan without any hesitation.

00:16:20.310 --> 00:16:21.810
That was a joke.

00:16:23.460 --> 00:16:24.890
It's a present.

00:16:24.890 --> 00:16:25.920
Take it.

00:16:27.520 --> 00:16:28.900
I don't want this...

00:16:28.900 --> 00:16:32.090
I upgraded it to version 2.67.

00:16:32.090 --> 00:16:34.110
What a pain.

00:16:34.110 --> 00:16:35.930
But I'll take it anyway.

00:16:38.660 --> 00:16:39.390
Bye.

00:16:45.430 --> 00:16:45.850
Kurisu!

00:16:45.850 --> 00:16:46.430
Right...

00:16:48.690 --> 00:16:50.100
This is for you!

00:16:57.680 --> 00:16:59.750
Where were you throwing that?

00:16:59.750 --> 00:17:01.270
Go get it.

00:17:01.270 --> 00:17:02.300
Jeez...

00:17:26.030 --> 00:17:27.220
<i>Okabe...</i>

00:17:27.930 --> 00:17:32.510
<i>I'm sure, whatever happens, you're going to suffer.</i>

00:17:33.100 --> 00:17:36.040
<i>Only you will remember me,</i>

00:17:36.040 --> 00:17:40.180
<i>in a world where no one else does.</i>

00:17:40.180 --> 00:17:42.850
<i>More than anyone else, you care for your friends,</i>

00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:45.410
<i>so that'll be painful for you.</i>

00:17:48.540 --> 00:17:49.430
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

00:17:51.200 --> 00:17:54.390
<i>But somehow, I'm glad you'll have that pain.</i>

00:17:55.440 --> 00:17:57.330
<i>Those times when you're sitting around the lab...</i>

00:17:57.810 --> 00:17:59.500
<i>When you drink a can of juice...</i>

00:17:59.930 --> 00:18:01.580
<i>When you walk around town...</i>

00:18:02.820 --> 00:18:05.650
<i>And someday, when you kiss someone.</i>

00:18:07.760 --> 00:18:09.520
<i>It doesn't have to be every time...</i>

00:18:09.520 --> 00:18:11.590
<i>It can be one time out of a hundred...</i>

00:18:11.590 --> 00:18:13.410
<i>But I'd like you to remember me.</i>

00:18:14.270 --> 00:18:16.720
<i>Because I'll be there...</i>

00:18:17.460 --> 00:18:21.840
<i>I'll be there, beyond the 1% barrier!</i>

00:18:23.860 --> 00:18:25.140
<i>Okabe...</i>

00:18:26.100 --> 00:18:27.100
<i>Okabe.</i>

00:18:28.150 --> 00:18:29.060
<i>Okabe!</i>

00:18:39.840 --> 00:18:40.990
Oh, man.

00:18:40.990 --> 00:18:42.320
Okarin, I found it.

00:18:42.320 --> 00:18:43.350
This is it...

00:18:43.350 --> 00:18:44.140
This is totally it!

00:18:45.070 --> 00:18:46.560
If we delete this...

00:18:46.560 --> 00:18:48.460
Mission complete.

00:18:49.680 --> 00:18:50.770
Okarin,

00:18:50.770 --> 00:18:51.600
are you okay?

00:18:53.760 --> 00:18:54.600
I'm fine...

00:18:55.610 --> 00:19:00.100
We now begin the final phase of Operation Verdandi!

00:19:00.770 --> 00:19:02.530
Our victory is nigh!

00:19:02.880 --> 00:19:05.960
We have overcome all conspiracies...

00:19:06.660 --> 00:19:08.880
Upholding our ideals to the last.

00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:12.810
And finally, we have fought through 
the battle of Ragnarok!

00:19:13.540 --> 00:19:17.500
I thank those who have worked so hard for me,

00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:19.520
to ensure this victory!

00:19:19.830 --> 00:19:24.180
I am grateful to all those I have had to sacrifice...

00:19:24.530 --> 00:19:28.620
What comes now is the world I wished for!

00:19:28.620 --> 00:19:31.290
This is all the choice of Steins Gate!

00:19:33.480 --> 00:19:34.770
The world...

00:19:36.470 --> 00:19:38.930
...will be rebuilt!

00:19:39.860 --> 00:19:40.970
<i>Kurisu...</i>

00:19:46.150 --> 00:19:47.340
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

00:19:48.090 --> 00:19:48.810
Okabe!

00:19:56.220 --> 00:19:57.530
Okabe...

00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:58.740
I'm also...

00:19:58.740 --> 00:19:59.560
Kurisu!

00:19:59.930 --> 00:20:02.720
I'm also in...

00:20:18.770 --> 00:20:19.760
Mayuri?

00:20:20.600 --> 00:20:22.670
Who is Lab Member 004?

00:20:22.670 --> 00:20:24.490
004?

00:20:26.080 --> 00:20:28.530
There isn't an 004.

00:20:34.830 --> 00:20:39.060
Now the battle of Ragnarok has ended!

00:20:39.060 --> 00:20:43.230
I, the mad scientist, Hououin Kyouma, 
have controlled time itself,

00:20:43.230 --> 00:20:46.630
foiling the Organization and SERN's schemes,

00:20:46.630 --> 00:20:49.810
and bringing about complete victory!

00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:52.770
The world's ruling structure has been reset!

00:20:52.770 --> 00:20:55.170
And a future of chaos awaits!

00:20:55.700 --> 00:20:59.270
This is the choice of Steins Gate!

00:20:59.270 --> 00:21:01.970
Okarin, it's all right.

00:21:03.120 --> 00:21:05.180
What are you saying?

00:21:05.180 --> 00:21:07.430
I've just issued a declaration of victory...

00:21:07.430 --> 00:21:10.500
You don't have to talk like that anymore.

00:21:11.240 --> 00:21:14.350
Mayushii is okay now.

00:21:14.560 --> 00:21:18.310
So you can cry for yourself, Okarin.

00:21:23.060 --> 00:21:24.970
<i>We no longer need the Phone Microwave.</i>

00:21:25.710 --> 00:21:29.210
<i>Because of it, I met Kurisu.</i>

00:21:30.230 --> 00:21:36.550
<i>But because of it, so many were hurt...</i>

00:21:38.330 --> 00:21:40.420
<i>Just as Hououin Kyouma has died,</i>

00:21:40.920 --> 00:21:43.140
<i>the Phone Microwave should die, as well.</i>

00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:48.850
<i>Living should mean no do-overs...</i>

00:21:50.430 --> 00:21:55.670
<i>This is for the best. Right, Kurisu?</i>

00:23:00.410 --> 00:23:01.270
Hello?

00:23:01.840 --> 00:23:04.020
Huh? Wh-Who's this?

00:23:04.880 --> 00:23:06.270
Dad?

00:23:06.270 --> 00:23:07.310
What?

00:23:07.310 --> 00:23:08.350
Okarin?

00:23:08.770 --> 00:23:11.780
Okarin, there's a mysterious girl 
who wants to talk to you!

00:23:12.350 --> 00:23:13.140
Who is this?

00:23:13.140 --> 00:23:15.980
Please come to the Radio Building's roof immediately!

00:23:16.770 --> 00:23:17.830
Who are you?

00:23:17.830 --> 00:23:20.700
I've come from the year 2036.

00:23:20.700 --> 00:23:23.340
I'm Hashida Itaru's daughter, Amane Suzuha!

00:23:23.340 --> 00:23:24.570
Suzuha?

00:23:25.280 --> 00:23:26.730
Wait!

00:23:26.730 --> 00:23:28.570
What are you doing here?

00:23:28.570 --> 00:23:31.090
Please believe what I'm about to tell you.

00:23:31.090 --> 00:23:34.010
You must stop World War III.

